			<h2 class="task-header task-header">if...else statements</h2>
			<p class="task-paragraph">Decision making is required when we want to execute a code only if a certain condition is satisfied.</p>
			<p class="task-paragraph">The if…elif…else statement is used in Python for decision making.</p>


      <h3>Syntax:</h3>
      <div class="command-examples" >
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples"><span class="command">if </span><span class="specific-command"> expression </span>:</p>
        <p class="task-paragraph code-examples text-spaces">statement(one)</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples"><span class="command">else </span>:</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples text-spaces">statement(two)</p>
      </div>

			<p>If the condition is true, then do the indented statements.</p>
			<p>If the condition is not true, then skip the indented statements and go to else condition.</p>

			<h3>Examples:</h1>
			<p class="task-paragraph">If the number is higher than 3, we print an appropriate message</p>
			<div class="command-examples" >
				<p class = "code-examples">num = 4 </p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples"><span class="command">if </span><span class="specific-command"> num > 3 </span>:</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples text-spaces">print("num is higher than 3")</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples"><span class="command">else </span>:</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples text-spaces">print("num is less than 3")</p>
			</div>

			<p>The above program will print "num is higher than 3"</p>

			<h3>Syntax of if...elif...else</h3>
			<div class="command-examples">
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples"><span class="command">if </span><span class="specific-command"> expression </span>:</p>
        <p class="task-paragraph code-examples text-spaces">statement(one)</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples"><span class="command">elif </span><span class="specific-command"> expression </span>:</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples text-spaces">statement(two)</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples"><span class="command">elif </span><span class="specific-command"> expression </span>:</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples text-spaces">statement(three)</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples"><span class="command">else </span>:</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples text-spaces">laststatement()</p>
			</div>
			<p>The elif is short for else if. It allows us to check for multiple expressions.</p>

			<p>If the condition for if is False, it checks the condition of the next elif block and so on.</p>

			<p>If all the conditions are False, body of else is executed.</p>

			<p>Only one block among the several if...elif...else blocks is executed according to the condition.</p>

			<p>The if block can have only one else block. But it can have multiple elif blocks.</p>

			<h3>Examples:</h1>
			<p class="task-paragraph">If the number is higher than 3, we print an appropriate message</p>
			<div class="command-examples" >
				<p class = "code-examples">num = 3 </p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples"><span class="command">if </span><span class="specific-command"> num > 3 </span>:</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples text-spaces">print("num is higher than 3")</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples"><span class="command">elif</span><span class="specific-command"> num == 3 </span> :</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples text-spaces">print("num equals 3")</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples"><span class="command">else </span>:</p>
				<p class="task-paragraph code-examples text-spaces">print("num is less than 3")</p>
			</div>
			<p>The above program will print "num is higher than 3"</p>
